    "texts": [
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Identification features",
            "shortText": "<p>Small and very delicate species consisting of thin, branching filaments each ending in a pair of strongly-incurved, claw-like tips. The filaments are strongly banded with alternating rings of small red cells and larger transparent ones, creating a distinctive beaded appearance. Often grows epiphytically on other algae, such as <i>Codium</i> spp.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_1_7565",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Adult size",
            "shortText": "<p>Typically about 30 mm tall, with filaments only about 0.25 mm wide.&nbsp;</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_2_7566",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Distribution",
            "shortText": "<p><u>Global:</u> Endemic to southern African.</p><p><u>Local/Regional:</u><i> </i>Namibia to about East London.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_3_7567",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Biology",
            "shortText": "<p>Often epiphytic of other algae and common both in algal turfs and attached to the fronds of other larger algae.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_4_7568",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Food / prey",
            "shortText": "<p>Photosynthetic.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_5_7569",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Reproduction",
            "shortText": "<p>Tetraspores oval and borne in the apical segments.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_6_7570",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Similar species",
            "shortText": "<p>There are several similar regional species in this and closely-related genera and these can be easily confused â€“ see Stegenga reference for a more detailed account of, and identification key to, west coast species.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_7_7571",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
